This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image synthesis using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). The paper also discusses the deep generative representations and their role in scene synthesis, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the spatial layout and configuration of scenes, which is related to the sub-category of Graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the layer-wise latent codes used in GANs, which is related to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
